 each. <P>"It is unfortunate that alot of EM is just not as good as the quest stuff,"<P>Alot? Umm please explain. Helm, BP, and Legs all add good-very good +wisdom along with primo AC. Bracers, per above, are better if you have 200 or greater wisdom without +wis bracers. That leaves arms,gloves,and boots. <P>Arms: EM: AC:15  +9 str  +7vs magic<BR>Quest armor: AC:11 +5 dex +5vs fire<P>Boots: EM: AC:15 +5 int +5 agi +7 vis cold<BR>Quest armor: AC:11 +6 vs disease<P>Gloves: EM:AC:12 +5 dex +5 int +7 vs fire.<BR>Quest armor: AC:12 +5 agi  +5vs cold.<P>I dont see how EM boots or arms can be considered anything but "much better" than the quest armor.<P>Gloves however are another matter being as they have the same AC. +5 agil would probably make them better than +5 int/+5 dex IF you get an AC increase from the added agility.<P>Please explain how "alot of EM is just not as good as the quest stuff". <BR>    </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Corii Se'Lune</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Weight of the Gods - <P>This is not a quest item from Sky, it is a dropped item.<P>Mine dropped off the Thunder Spirit princess on island 1 but I am told that was an extremely lucky drop.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"> The other one I saw drop was on the third island.<P><P>------------------<BR>Corii Se'Lune<BR>Devoted of Quellious<BR>53rd Rank Vicar<BR><A HREF="http://succoringwinds.dynhost.com" TARGET=_blank> Succoring Winds </A>- Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mlar D'Kath</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If they where obtainable i would wear them.Even if you had 200wis before these the extra 6 wis means that in another slot you could drop a wis item for a high AC/Mana one.ie drop a 6 wis ring for an AC or a mana ring.Also not all clerics go flat out for 200 at all costs,myself im at 197 and already have items that could put me above 200,but i would take a severe AC hit doing so.<P><BR>Mlar D'Kath<BR>Priest of Innoruuk</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
